@cache
application uses Redis caching improve performance
-Cache TTL 300s
-Cache invalidation handled automatically
-Session data not cached because security concerns
@error_handling
API returns standard HTTP error codes. errors include JSON body message field
Errors should logged debugging purposes. system must handle rate limiting gracefully. Users may retry after specified cooldown period
@dependencies
API depends following services:
-Database (PostgreSQL)
-Cache (Redis)
-Authentication service (OAuth2 provider)
-Notification service (optional)
